            "answer_text": "Coins have tolerances, but quarters (and dimes and half-dollars) are nominally $20/pound, as minted. Note that the Mint publishes their actual weight in grains convered to grams by an approximate 64.8 mg/grain, ie slightly wrong. $1E6 x 1 lb/$20 = 50 000 lb more or less (remember tolerances, which get worse as coins wear and/or get dirty in circulation) ",
